KCA University celebrated its inaugural Founders Day on Friday evening at the Radisson Blu Hotel in Upperhill, Nairobi.This is an annual event where the university celebrates its birth, rich past and its promising future.The celebration was held as a black tie fundraising dinner, dance and award ceremony (gala dinner) to bring together university founders, alumni, staff, students and other distinguished members of the society.As part of the celebration, KCA university launched an endowment fund to facilitate scholarships where proceeds from the gala dinner would go towards the scholarship endowment fund to support the lives of young people who would otherwise not have an opportunity to attain a university education.Afro-pop band Sauti Sol were the star entertainment of the evening.